message.content:
Below is one worked‐through solution showing how the two grouped “figures” in the main image can be broken down into their individual blocks, matched to the dictionary, and then assembled step by step.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

■ Left (taller) structure
 • Block Count: 5 total  
   – 2 orange cylinders on the bottom (“legs”)  
   – 1 long yellow rectangular block bridging those cylinders  
   – 1 orange cylinder stacked above the yellow block (“neck”)  
   – 1 yellow half‐cylinder on top  
 • Layering (from bottom to top):
   – Layer 1: Two orange cylinders side by side  
   – Layer 2: Yellow rectangular block across the top of both cylinders  
   – Layer 3: Orange cylinder centered on the yellow block  
   – Layer 4: Yellow half‐cylinder resting on that top cylinder  

■ Right (shorter) structure
 • Block Count: 6 total  
   – 1 orange cylinder in the center  
   – 2 orange triangular wedges at floor level (one on each side)  
   – 2 small blue rectangular blocks standing between the cylinder and the wedges  
   – 1 orange triangular wedge capping the cylinder on top  
 • Layering (conceptually):
   – Layer 1: Center orange cylinder plus the two large orange wedges at the base  
   – Layer 2: Two upright blue rectangular blocks flanking the cylinder  
   – Layer 3: One orange triangular wedge perched on top of the cylinder  

In total, there are 11 blocks used (5 on the left structure + 6 on the right).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Below are the chosen dictionary indices to match color, shape, **and** orientation exactly (no further rotations allowed):

● Left Structure  
   – Orange cylinders → three copies of Block #6  
   – Yellow rectangular bridging block → Block #5  
   – Yellow half‐cylinder on top → Block #7  

● Right Structure  
   – Orange cylinder (center) → one copy of Block #6  
   – Blue rectangular side blocks → two copies of Block #1  
   – Orange triangular wedges → three wedges in orientations matching the figure.  
     A consistent choice is:  
       • Base left wedge → Block #14  
       • Base right wedge → Block #16  
       • Top wedge → Block #13  

Hence the required block indices are:
{6, 6, 6, 5, 7} for the left group and {6, 1, 1, 13, 14, 16} for the right.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY SEQUENCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Below is one possible order in which to place/move each selected block:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 6   // Left structure, first orange cylinder (leg)
  Step2:  Move block with index 6   // Left structure, second orange cylinder (leg)
  Step3:  Move block with index 5   // Place yellow rectangular block bridging the 2 cylinders
  Step4:  Move block with index 6   // Orange cylinder stacked on the yellow block (neck)
  Step5:  Move block with index 7   // Yellow half‐cylinder on top

  Step6:  Move block with index 6   // Right structure, center orange cylinder
  Step7:  Move block with index 14  // Left orange wedge at floor level
  Step8:  Move block with index 16  // Right orange wedge at floor level
  Step9:  Move block with index 1   // Blue rectangle on left side
  Step10: Move block with index 1   // Blue rectangle on right side
  Step11: Move block with index 13  // Orange wedge on top of cylinder
}

Following those steps with the exact blocks/orientations listed will re‐create the two structures exactly as shown.
